./frontend/node_modules/@babel/core/lib/transformation/file/file.js.map\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n./frontend/node_modules/@babel/core/lib/transformation/file/merge-map.js.map\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n./frontend/node_modules/@babel/core/lib/transformation/file/generate.js\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n./frontend/node_modules/@babel/core/lib/transformation/file/babel-7-helpers.cjs.map\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n./frontend/node_modules/@babel/core/lib/transformation/file/merge-map.js\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\", \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"command\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"/bin/zsh -lc \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"rg --files -g 'AGENTS.md' -g 'README*' -g 'base_prompt.md' -g 'prompts/**' -g 'frontend/**' -g 'backend/**' .\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\", \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"exit_code\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": 0, \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"id\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"item_3\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\", \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"status\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"completed\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\", \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"type\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"command_execution\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"}, \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"type\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"item.completed\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"}, \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"task_display_context\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": {\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"event_number\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": 12, \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"prompt_index\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": 4, \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"prompt_name\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"03 \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\u2014 Scaffold the FastAPI Backend\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\", \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"prompt_total\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": 100}, \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"timestap\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"2026-03-31T21:21:41-07:00\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"}\\\\\\\\nprompts/05-backend-settings-and-secrets-loading.yolopilot.md:672:    prompts/03-fastapi-scaffold.yolopilot.jsonlines:19:{\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"color\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"cyan\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\", \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"emoji\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\ud83d\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\udee0\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\ufe0f\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\", \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"event_type\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"Command Finished\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\", \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"message\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"completed, exit 0: /bin/zsh -lc \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"sed -n '1,220p' README.md\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\", \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"raw_event\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": {\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"item\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": {\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"aggregated_output\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"# Storyteller\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nStoryteller is a local-first, full-stack app for creating bedtime stories from first idea to finished text and finished narration audio. The product is session-based: the first meaningful screen is a past-sessions view where a user can resume work in progress, reopen a completed story, or start a new session.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nThis repository currently contains the first scaffold for that system. The project charter in this README and the supporting docs define the product and architecture that later prompts will implement.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n## Product Vision\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nThe app should feel like a guided bedtime story studio, not a generic prompt box. A user should be able to:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- See past sessions first and continue where they left off.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- Collaborate through both chat and direct UI controls.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- Move through a structured planning workflow before long-form writing starts.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- Watch story composition and audio generation progress in real time.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- Return later to read, listen, download, or revise completed work.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nThe tone of the product should stay calm, readable, and trustworthy. Wonder, mystery, and adventure are welcome, but bedtime suitability is a hard requirement: emotional stakes should resolve safely and the ending should feel restful.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n## Required Story Workflow\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nThe application is being built around this ordered workflow:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n1. Genre selection\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n2. Tone selection\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n3. Story setup / free-form brief\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n4. Story pitches\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n5. Character sheet\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n6. Save-the-Cat beat sheet\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n7. Story setup preferences such as word count, runtime, and chapters\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n8. Composition\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n9. Audio configuration and audio generation\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n10. Finalize / read / listen / download\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nEach stage must be durable, resumable, and editable. Chat messages can propose actions in the workflow, and direct UI actions must also be reflected back into the session chat log as compact summaries.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n## Fixed Technical Decisions\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nThese choices are not optional for this project:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- Frontend: React + Vite + TypeScript\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- Backend: Python + FastAPI\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- Structured data: PostgreSQL\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- Blob storage: file-backed GCS emulator in local development\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- Local orchestration: Docker Compose\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- Secrets handling: local `secrets.yaml`, never committed to git\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- AI access: Gemini 3.1 family behind backend-owned adapters and services\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nTwo architectural rules follow from those constraints:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- The browser must never hold provider secrets or call Gemini directly.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- Long-running story composition and narration generation must be durable background jobs with resumable server-side state.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nMore detail is in [docs/product-brief.md](/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/docs/product-brief.md) and [docs/architecture-overview.md](/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/docs/architecture-overview.md).\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n## Local Development Expectations\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nThe repo is intended to run locally with Docker Compose. At the current scaffold stage:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- `frontend/` contains a Vite React app served on `http://localhost:8566`\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- `backend/` contains a FastAPI app served on `http://localhost:8565`\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- `infra/compose/` holds the canonical Compose file for local orchestration\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- `tools/webapp-qa/` contains the browser automation container used for local UI verification\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nStart the current stack with:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n```bash\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n./scripts/dev-compose.sh up --build\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n```\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nThe current scaffold does not yet include PostgreSQL or the file-backed GCS emulator, but both are required parts of the target system and will be added through later prompt work. `secrets.yaml` is already gitignored and reserved for local-only credentials.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n## Repository Shape\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n```text\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\u251c\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\u2500\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\u2500 backend/\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\u2502   \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\u251c\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\u2500\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\u2500 app/\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\u2502   \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\u2502   \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\u251c\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\u2500\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\u2500 main.py\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\u2502   \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\u2502   \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\u2514\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\u2500\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\u2500 worker/\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\u2502   \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\u251c\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\u2500\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\u2500 migrations/\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\u2502   \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\u251c\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\u2500\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\u2500 Dockerfile\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\u2502   \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\u251c\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\u2500\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\u2500 README.md\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\u2502   \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\u2514\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\u2500\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\u2500 requirements.txt\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\u251c\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\u2500\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\u2500 docs/\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\u251c\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\u2500\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\u2500 frontend/\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\u251c\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\u2500\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\u2500 infra/\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\u2502   \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\u251c\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\u2500\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\u2500 compose/\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\u2502   \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\u2502   \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\u2514\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\u2500\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\u2500 docker-compose.yml\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\u2502   \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\u2514\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\u2500\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\u2500 persistence/\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\u251c\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\u2500\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\u2500 prompts/\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\u251c\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\u2500\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\u2500 scripts/\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\u251c\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\u2500\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\u2500 test-assets/\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\u2514\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\u2500\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\u2500 tools/\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\u2514\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\u2500\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\u2500 webapp-qa/\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n```\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- `frontend/`: browser client and TypeScript UI foundation\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- `backend/`: API code, worker home, and migration home\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- `infra/`: Compose definitions and infrastructure notes\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- `docs/`: product notes, architecture notes, and future ADRs\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- `scripts/`: developer entrypoints such as `dev-compose.sh`\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- `test-assets/`: reusable fixtures for UI, audio, and integration testing\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- `prompts/`: sequential build prompts and task summaries\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- `tools/`: local QA and developer tooling\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n## What Success Looks Like\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nA new engineer should be able to open this repository and quickly understand:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- the first screen is the past-sessions home for resume, edit, and create flows\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- the story workflow is staged and ordered\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- the final product writes stories and generates narration audio durably\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- the backend owns AI access, long-running jobs, and persistent state\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\", \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"command\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"/bin/zsh -lc \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"sed -n '1,220p' README.md\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\", \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"exit_code\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": 0, \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"id\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"item_6\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\", \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"status\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"completed\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\", \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"type\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"command_execution\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"}, \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"type\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"item.completed\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"}, \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"task_display_context\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": {\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"event_number\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": 19, \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"prompt_index\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": 4, \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"prompt_name\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"03 \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\u2014 Scaffold the FastAPI Backend\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\", \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"prompt_total\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": 100}, \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"timestap\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"2026-03-31T21:21:54-07:00\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"}\\\\\\\\nprompts/05-backend-settings-and-secrets-loading.yolopilot.md:673:    prompts/03-fastapi-scaffold.yolopilot.jsonlines:33:{\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"color\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"cyan\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\", \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"emoji\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\ud83d\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\udee0\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\ufe0f\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\", \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"event_type\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"Command Finished\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\", \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"message\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"completed, exit 0: /bin/zsh -lc \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"sed -n '1,260p' docs/architecture-overview.md\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\", \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"raw_event\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": {\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"item\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": {\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"aggregated_output\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"# Architecture Overview\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n## System Picture\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nStoryteller is a full-stack application with a browser client, a backend-owned workflow engine, durable relational state, durable object storage, and resumable background jobs.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n```text\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nReact + Vite client\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n        |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n        v\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nFastAPI API layer\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n        |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n        +--> domain services and policy layer\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n        |         |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n        |         +--> AI adapters for planning, composition, and narration\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n        |         |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n        |         +--> repositories for sessions, workflow state, jobs, and event log\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n        |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n        +--> background workers for composition and audio generation\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n                  |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n                  +--> PostgreSQL for durable structured state\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n                  +--> file-backed GCS emulator for artifacts and intermediate blobs\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n```\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n## Why Gemini Calls Must Stay on the Backend\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nAll Gemini access belongs on the server side for four reasons:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n1. Secrets control: provider credentials live in local `secrets.yaml` and must never enter the browser.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n2. Policy enforcement: chat-to-UI actions and workflow transitions need deterministic server validation before the model can change session state.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n3. Durable orchestration: prompts, structured outputs, retries, and model selection need to be coordinated with persistent session data and job records.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n4. Provider flexibility: keeping Gemini behind backend adapters lets the app keep a stable internal interface while model IDs, structured output tactics, or narration providers evolve.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nThe frontend should only call the backend's API and subscribe to backend-owned progress events.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n## Why Composition and Audio Must Use Resumable Server-Side Jobs\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nComposition and narration are long-running operations that cannot safely live inside request threads or browser memory. They need server-side jobs because:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- a user must be able to refresh the page or return later without losing progress\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- partial story text and audio segments need durable checkpoints\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- progress updates need a single source of truth that both chat and UI can observe\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- retries, cancellation, and resume logic need explicit job state rather than transient in-memory state\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nThe durable model should include job records, segment records, asset metadata, and an event log that can reconstruct session progress after interruption.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n## Intended Backend Shape\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nThe target backend should separate concerns explicitly:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- `api/`: HTTP routes and websocket endpoints\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- `settings/`: environment and secrets loading\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- `db/`: database engine, migrations, and persistence setup\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- `models/`: typed domain models and persistence schemas\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- `repositories/`: database access for sessions, events, jobs, and assets\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- `services/`: workflow logic and policy enforcement\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- `ai/`: Gemini planning, composition, and narration adapters\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- `worker/`: background job execution for writing and audio\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- `storage/`: object storage abstraction over the local GCS emulator\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n## Durable Domain Concepts\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nThe system should persist the following concepts as first-class records:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- Session\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- Workflow stage\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- Event log\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- Selected genre\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- Selected tone\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- Story brief\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- Pitch batch and selected pitch\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- Character batch and selected character sheet\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- Beat sheet\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- Story setup preferences\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- Outline or chapter plan\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- Continuity bible\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- Composition job and segments\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- Audio job and segments\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- Asset metadata\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n## Current Repository State\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nThe repository currently contains an initial scaffold:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- `frontend/`: Vite React TypeScript app\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- `backend/`: FastAPI app\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- `backend/migrations/`: reserved home for database schema history\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- `backend/app/worker/`: reserved home for background job runners\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- `infra/compose/docker-compose.yml`: local frontend, backend, and browser QA services\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- `infra/persistence/`: notes for persistent local infrastructure data\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- `scripts/dev-compose.sh`: convenience entrypoint for the Compose stack\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- `tools/webapp-qa/`: containerized browser automation support\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nPostgreSQL, the file-backed GCS emulator, background workers, and most domain layers are still planned work. This document records the required direction so later prompts can extend the scaffold without changing the architectural contract.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\", \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"command\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"/bin/zsh -lc \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"sed -n '1,260p' docs/architecture-overview.md\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\", \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"exit_code\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": 0, \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"id\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"item_14\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\", \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"status\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"completed\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\", \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"type\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"command_execution\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"}, \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"type\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"item.completed\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"}, \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"task_display_context\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": {\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"event_number\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": 33, \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"prompt_index\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": 4, \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"prompt_name\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"03 \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\u2014 Scaffold the FastAPI Backend\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\", \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"prompt_total\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": 100}, \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"timestap\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"2026-03-31T21:22:00-07:00\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"}\\\\\\\\nprompts/05-backend-settings-and-secrets-loading.yolopilot.md:681:    prompts/03-fastapi-scaffold.yolopilot.jsonlines:56:{\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"color\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"cyan\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\", \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"emoji\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\ud83d\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\udee0\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\ufe0f\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\", \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"event_type\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"Command Finished\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\", \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"message\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"completed, exit 0: /bin/zsh -lc \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"sed -n '1,260p' backend/app/main.py\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\", \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"raw_event\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": {\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"item\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": {\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"aggregated_output\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"from __future__ import annotations\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nimport logging\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nfrom contextlib import asynccontextmanager\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nfrom typing import AsyncIterator\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nfrom fastapi import FastAPI\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nfrom fastapi.middleware.cors import CORSMiddleware\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nfrom app.api.router import router as api_router\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nfrom app.api.v1.router import router as api_v1_router\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nfrom app.settings import AppSettings, get_settings\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nlogger = logging.getLogger(__name__)\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\ndef configure_logging(settings: AppSettings) -> None:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    logging.basicConfig(\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n        level=getattr(logging, settings.log_level, logging.INFO),\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n        format=\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"%(levelname)s %(name)s %(message)s\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    )\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n@asynccontextmanager\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nasync def lifespan(app: FastAPI) -> AsyncIterator[None]:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    settings = get_settings()\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    configure_logging(settings)\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    app.state.settings = settings\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    logger.info(\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n        \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"Starting %s in %s mode on %s:%s\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n        settings.app_name,\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n        settings.environment,\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n        settings.host,\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n        settings.port,\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    )\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    yield\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    logger.info(\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"Stopping %s\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\", settings.app_name)\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\ndef create_app() -> FastAPI:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    settings = get_settings()\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    app = FastAPI(\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n        title=settings.app_name,\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n        version=settings.version,\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n        lifespan=lifespan,\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    )\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    app.add_middleware(\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n        CORSMiddleware,\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n        allow_origins=list(settings.cors_allowed_origins),\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n        allow_credentials=True,\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n        allow_methods=[\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"*\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"],\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n        allow_headers=[\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"*\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"],\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    )\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    app.include_router(api_router)\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    app.include_router(api_v1_router, prefix=settings.api_v1_prefix)\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    return app\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\napp = create_app()\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\", \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"command\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"/bin/zsh -lc \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"sed -n '1,260p' backend/app/main.py\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\", \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"exit_code\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": 0, \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"id\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"item_26\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\", \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"status\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"completed\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\", \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"type\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"command_execution\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"}, \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"type\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"item.completed\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"}, \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"task_display_context\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": {\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"event_number\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": 56, \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"prompt_index\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": 4, \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"prompt_name\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"03 \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\u2014 Scaffold the FastAPI Backend\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\", \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"prompt_total\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": 100}, \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"timestap\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"2026-03-31T21:26:05-07:00\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"}\\\\\\\\nprompts/05-backend-settings-and-secrets-loading.yolopilot.md:682:    prompts/03-fastapi-scaffold.yolopilot.jsonlines:57:{\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"color\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"cyan\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\", \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"emoji\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\ud83d\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\udee0\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\ufe0f\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\", \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"event_type\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"Command Finished\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\", \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"message\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"completed, exit 0: /bi