{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_58","type":"command_execution","command":"/bin/zsh -lc \"sed -n '1,220p' prompts/83-artifact-packaging-and-links.md\"","aggregated_output":"# 83 — Artifact Packaging and Download Links\n\nRead `base_prompt.md` first and preserve all prior prompt work.\n\n## Objective\n\nExpose all generated artifacts coherently so the user can retrieve the outputs they care about without hunting.\n\n## Build\n- Create a backend endpoint that returns a session’s current artifact inventory: final story text, docx export, final audio, and any useful preview assets.\n- Build the finalize stage download area with clear labels and readiness indicators.\n- Handle missing or outdated artifacts explicitly.\n\n## Deliverables\n\n- Artifact inventory endpoint\n- Finalize download section\n- Outdated/missing artifact messaging\n\n## Acceptance checks\n\n- The user can see what artifacts exist for the session at a glance.\n- The UI distinguishes ready, generating, failed, and stale artifacts.\n- Download affordances map to real backend assets reliably.\n\n## Notes\n\nOne clean artifact panel beats scattered buttons.\n\n## Suggested commit label\n\n`feat(prompt-83): artifact packaging and links`\n","exit_code":0,"status":"completed"}}
{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_59","type":"agent_message","text":"Plan:\n1. Inspect the current asset/public URL path end to end and map the smallest server-side access layer that can replace direct emulator links.\n2. Implement backend asset access: route(s), service, content headers, and range-aware streaming for audio, plus tests.\n3. Close the story-export gap by publishing a `.docx` asset from the canonical final story text if it is still missing, then cover it with tests.\n4. Update frontend asset types and stage logic to use backend-mediated artifact URLs, add finalize/download affordances and chat-triggered download handling, then extend UI tests.\n5. Run targeted backend/frontend tests, relevant lint/build/type checks, browser verification through the running app, and write the required reviewer summary file last."}}
{"type":"item.started","item":{"id":"item_60","type":"todo_list","items":[{"text":"Inspect existing asset and frontend finalize/audio flows to define a backend-mediated artifact access design","completed":true},{"text":"Implement backend asset access service, routes, and response model updates with tests","completed":false},{"text":"Publish or regenerate the story docx export from canonical final story text if absent, with tests","completed":false},{"text":"Update frontend asset hooks and finalize/audio UI to use backend artifact URLs and add tests","completed":false},{"text":"Run verification, browser checks, commit checkpoints, and write the final summary file","completed":false}]}}
