{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_185","type":"agent_message","text":"Implemented backend-mediated artifact access and wrote the required reviewer summary at [summary.md](/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/.yolopilot/runs/20260331T205548_storyteller_prompt_pack/78_download_endpoints_and_object_access/summary.md).\n\nThe main changes are:\n- new session-scoped artifact endpoints for named artifacts and concrete asset content, including byte-range support for audio in [`sessions.py`](/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/backend/app/api/v1/routes/sessions.py)\n- new backend services for asset resolution and on-demand `.docx` export generation in [`asset_access.py`](/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/backend/app/services/asset_access.py) and [`story_exports.py`](/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/backend/app/services/story_exports.py)\n- hydrated asset views now expose backend access paths instead of direct emulator URLs in [`session_hydration.py`](/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/backend/app/services/session_hydration.py)\n- frontend playback/download wiring now goes through backend URLs, with finalize download controls and chat `download_asset` handling in [`AudioSettingsStage.tsx`](/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/frontend/src/features/session/AudioSettingsStage.tsx), [`FinalizeStage.tsx`](/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/frontend/src/features/session/FinalizeStage.tsx), [`SessionWorkspacePage.tsx`](/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/frontend/src/pages/session/SessionWorkspacePage.tsx), and [`sessionArtifacts.ts`](/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/frontend/src/features/session/sessionArtifacts.ts)\n\nVerification completed:\n- `cd backend && ruff check ...` passed\n- `cd backend && pytest tests/test_session_api.py tests/test_session_hydration_service.py tests/test_story_export_service.py` passed, 52 tests\n- `cd frontend && npm test src/features/session/FinalizeStage.test.tsx src/features/session/AudioSettingsStage.test.tsx src/features/session/sessionArtifacts.test.ts` passed, 9 tests\n- `cd frontend && npm run lint` passed\n- `cd frontend && npm run build` passed\n\nBrowser verification was attempted through the repo’s Docker-based QA flow, but Docker Desktop never exposed a reachable daemon on this machine, so no compose/browser screenshot pass was possible. I documented that limit in the summary."}}
